* .NET Core Version: Preview6 27720-09
* Have you experienced this same bug with .NET Framework?: No

**Problem description:**

Keyboard accelerators on MenuStrip are ignored. For instance, when the File menu is open and you press 'S' to save, nothing happens, despite the menu item text being "&Save". Also, the keyboard arrows don't work fully - when you press up-arrow on the first menu item, it doesn't cycle to the last item on the menu as it does in .NET Framework (and every other Windows app). This makes it hard work to navigate to the last item on the menu.

(Note that this bug was likely introduced around Preview5. In earlier .NET Core previews, I recall menu navigation working correctly.)

**Minimal repro:**

```
var file = new ToolStripMenuItem ("File");

file.DropDownItems.Add ("&New");
file.DropDownItems.Add ("&Open");
file.DropDownItems.Add ("&Save");
file.DropDownItems.Add ("Save &as");

var main = new MenuStrip ();
main.Items.Add (file);

var form = new Form { MainMenuStrip = main };
form.Controls.Add (main);

form.Show();
```
